# PersAI session continuity

- Read in order before implementing: `AGENTS.md`, `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md`, `docs/CHANGELOG.md`, `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, `docs/API-BOUNDARY.md`, `docs/DATA-MODEL.md`, `docs/TEST-PLAN.md`, then any ADRs referenced by the **user's explicit task** only.
- **Active founder-opened program:** ADR-147 is the bounded Assistant Roles and Effective Skills orchestration program. Role belongs to each exact Assistant (including every Assistant in a B2B multi-assistant account); existing Skill/Scenario/Knowledge/runtime mechanics remain intact. S0 is accepted; S1 schema/expand, S2 role-only API/runtime/prompt, S3 user Role UX, S4 Admin Role constructor/MCP, and S5a Release-B contract cutover are implemented and parent-audited CLEAN; S5a required two rejected audits before final fail-closed gate hardening. S5b physical contract/drop is implemented locally against `d8195d1d`; two focused-evidence audits rejected then repaired, final re-audit is CLEAN, isolated 189-migration/semantic fixture proof passes, and the complete local repository gate passes; Release C is not deployed. S5b performs idempotent plan JSON Skill-limit cleanup then drops `assistant_skill_assignments` / `AssistantSkillAssignmentStatus`. Release B `a225143e` is deployed through healthy bot pin `4c28dd52`; CI, migration, exact-revision inventory, and operator-accessible Role/runtime/MCP acceptance passed. Authenticated B2B acceptance proved three independently addressed Assistants and live `Маркетолог · Instagram-карусель` header indication; repair commit `d8195d1d` is present. Commit/one final push precede migration-gated Release C deploy. Existing Cursor chats retain their attached old MCP schema; reload the server then open a new Agent chat. Implementation uses one sequential slice at a time. Cursor Grok 4.5 is the default subagent; GPT-5.4 is used only when stronger reasoning is necessary or Grok fails. Role UI is fully RU/EN, concise, premium, system-consistent; Admin Roles follows Admin Skills. ADR-146 is closed after S6 live acceptance. ADR-078, ADR-102, ADR-105–ADR-115, and the other closed numbered programs in `docs/ADR/` remain **closed archive**; do not reopen them or re-derive scope from them.
- Treat `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md` as the source of truth for the latest completed checkpoint and the user's next stated priority.
- Treat `docs/CHANGELOG.md` as the source of truth for what has actually landed.
- If ADR, handoff, changelog, and code disagree, stop and reconcile docs before code changes.
- One session = one bounded slice unless the user explicitly asks for broader work. New product/architecture waves require an explicit user priority and usually a **new ADR** before implementation.
- At session start, restate: task scope, purpose, likely affected files/modules, and what is out of scope.
- Start only from a clean git tree; if dirty, stop and report. Record baseline SHA in the handoff when the slice changes repo truth.
- Keep the architecture fully PersAI-native. Do not reintroduce OpenClaw runtime/deploy wiring, compatibility shims, filesystem-owned session state, or TODO scaffolding.
- Touch native OpenClaw only if historical analysis explicitly requires it and a PersAI-side change is insufficient.
- Before ending the session, update `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md`, update `docs/CHANGELOG.md` if repo truth changed, update or add an ADR only when long-term system truth changed, and state the next recommended step.
